Title: Cheddar
Description: A hard, sharp-tasting cheese which is aged anywhere from 3-24 months.

Title: Wensleydale
Description: A medium cheese, somewhat crumble. It is aged for three to six months.

Title: Brie
Description: A soft-ripened cow's milk cheese with an edible rind.

Title: Colby
Description: An orange semi-hard cheese made in a process similar to that for cheddar.

Title: Camembert
Description: A creamy, soft-ripened cheese from Camembert in Normandy, France.

Title: Hoop cheese
Description: A simple cows-milk cheese common to the south-eastern United States.

Title: Edam cheese
Description: A semi-hard cheese with a nutty flavor. It is usually sold with a coat of red wax.

Title: Feta
Description: A crumbly white cheese which is aged in brine.

Title: Taleggio
Description: A washed-rind cheese of a variety which has existed since Roman times.

Title: Cotija
Description: An aged white cheese with a salty flavor.
